![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/39ff3dc2-b9b3-4e7b-89a7-ce307666ebaf/Knightfight.png?format=original)

Get ready to witness the ultimate showdown in Gotham! DC Comics is set to unleash **Knightfight**, a new Batman-centric event that promises to be a thrilling, action-packed ride. Tying directly into the massive **DC K.O.** crossover, _Knightfight_ pits the Dark Knight against the most challenging opponents he could ever face: his own sidekicks!

* * *

## **Batman's Most Personal Battle Yet**

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/f384c0e0-9b4f-423e-80a7-ee7f5b102310/Knightfight.png?format=original)

In a recent interview, legendary writer Scott Snyder pulled back the curtain on this highly anticipated series, revealing it is a deeply personal journey for the Caped Crusader. **Knightfight** features Batman battling alternate versions of his former Robins who have grown up to become their own versions of the Caped Crusader. Snyder describes it as "Batman's journey through Hell."

This epic event is spearheaded by the dynamic team of writer **Joshua Williamson** with a little help from Scott Snyder and the phenomenal art of **Dan Mora**. The creative powerhouse is set to deliver "pure comic book joy with a lot of heart," according to Snyder.

* * *

## **A Tie-In to DC's "King Omega" Event**

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/b3a36696-2035-44fb-827a-2d0772beee75/DC-K.O.-FIRST-TEN-BRACKET-REVEALS.webp?format=original)

**Knightfight** is part of the larger **DC K.O.** event, where heroes are forced to compete in a cosmic tournament. The event's title, which stands for **King Omega**, refers to an omnipotent Darkseid who has become the "totality of Omega energy." The tournament is meant to find a champion to face him. As part of this, DC has announced "Fight Month" in December, featuring various character matches, including one written by Snyder himself!

Snyder also revealed a deeper, more personal meaning to the larger story. While _Knightfight_ focuses on Batman's emotional gauntlet, the overarching **DC K.O.** event is a personal Superman story, exploring what Snyder thinks makes the Man of Steel a truly great character.

* * *

Get ready for an explosive November when _Knightfight_ hits comic book stores, and prepare for a series that is set to be one of the most exciting Batman stories in years!

_(Source: Scott Snyder's recent interview as reported by Bleeding Cool and other news outlets.)_

